{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487137"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:58:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:58:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"260"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/260"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.66,0.05,0.15,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"260"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58903"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/260"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"260"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44312"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"1172"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"2078"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"10962"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3725"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18376"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42043"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58903","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/58903"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a one-hour history of constant, dull and heavy central chest pain. It does not radiate but is associated with dyspnoea and diaphoresis. He had returned from an overseas trip to the Philippines yesterday, where he was hospitalised in intensive care for pneumonia for five days. He has experienced a dry cough since discharge from hospital. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications, though has been taking a course of oral antimicrobials since discharge from hospital.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears pale and breathless. His pulse rate is 95/min, blood pressure 145/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, SpO2 94% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. Cardiorespiratory examination demonstrates poor air entry at the right lung base with associated bronchial breathing. Heart sounds are dual with a soft systolic murmur present at left sternal border. His abdomen is soft and non-tender. An initial electrocardiogram shows 2 mm ST depression in leads I, II and V4-6. His investigations show a creatinine of 105 \u00b5mol/L (45-90) and an initial high-sensitivity troponin T measures 225 ng/L (\u003C30).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Wellen\u0027s syndrome","Non-ST elevation myocardial infarction","Coronary vasospasm","Pericarditis","Troponin rise due to renal impairment"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Enon-ST elevation myocardial infarction (NSTEMI)\u003C/strong\u003E is made on the basis of an ECG showing ischaemic ST segment or T wave changes (other than ST elevation) in the setting of an elevated troponin. With modern high-sensitivity troponin assays, a repeat measurement should be performed at 2 hours to detect dynamic changes. The combination of typical symptoms, ECG changes, and elevated troponin is diagnostic.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough this patient has a mildly elevated creatinine, indicating \u003Cstrong\u003Erenal impairment\u003C/strong\u003E, the elevation in his \u003Cstrong\u003Etroponin\u003C/strong\u003E level is disproportionate to this, and a repeat troponin in 2 hours will likely show a further increase reflective of dynamic change indicative of acute myocardial injury.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoronary artery vasospasm\u003C/strong\u003E, while a possible cause of myocardial infarction, is much less common than atherosclerotic disease in this patient, and would require an angiogram for diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPericarditis\u003C/strong\u003E would typically present with sharp pleuritic chest pain and diffuse ST elevation with PR depression on ECG, neither of which are present here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWellens syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E refers to an ECG pattern of deeply inverted or biphasic T waves in leads V2-3, which is highly specific for a critical stenosis of the left anterior descending artery, and can reflect a need for urgent intervention. This pattern is not present in this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cardiac chest pain and elevated troponins likely indicate an MI; in the absence of ST elevation this is termed non-ST elevation MI (NSTEMI)","High-sensitivity troponin should be repeated at 2 hours to detect dynamic changes"],"references":["Pollack et al. Contemporary NSTEMI management: the role of the hospitalist. Hosp Pract. 2020;48(1):1-11. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31815570/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44312"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"260"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44312","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44312"},"attributes":{"c